<TITLE> Rono joins CPB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com)  A faction of the traditionally Pekingite Workers' Party of Bangladesh has merged with the Muscovite Communist Party. Senior leaders of the two parties announced their union at a press conference after a joint meeting on Friday. Haidar Akbar Khan Rono, head of a Workers' Party faction, has been elected presidium member of the strengthened Communist Party of Bangladesh (CPB). Md Habibur Rahman and Shahriar Md Firoz of the Workers' Party were elected CPB central committee members. CPB president Manzurul Ahsan Khan said that these decisions were taken as part of the unification process of the two parties.
